(22, 'The Troubles', 'The troubles,troubles,PIRA,Provisional Irish Republican Army (PIRA) attack,Provisional Irish Republican Army (PIRA) attack in London,PIRA attacks,history of PIRA,hidden history of the troubles,hidden history of PIRA.', 'The attacks on London were only one part of a 30-year conflict referred to as the ‘The Troubles’, which started in the late 1960’s and ended in 1998 with the signing of a peace treaty called the Good Friday agreement. Between 1973 and 1997 the Provisional Irish Republican Army (PIRA) carried out almost 500 attacks on the British mainland.'),
