(78, 'Hankey Place', 'A peculiar site peppered around London are odd looking metal fences. To a casual passer-by the oddness would not be picked up on but have a closer look and you can see metal fences that have peculiar curves in their horizontal bars. \r\n\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n\r\nThese are not a fancy design template ordered up en masse in post-war Britain but are in fact recycled WW2 Air Raid Precautions Department (ARP) steel stretchers that have been recycled as street fencing. The unusual curves are the stretcher handles.\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://hidden-history.com/public/assets/images/arp-stretchers-image1-mobile.jpg\" alt=\"Arp Stretchers\" width=\"auto\" height=\"auto\"> <sub><q>Arp Stretchers converted into fences. <i>Source: wikimedia commons </i></q></sub>\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n60’000 of these stretchers were produced during WW2 to cater for expected casualties from German bombing raids and come the end of the conflict they were very much surplus to requirements.\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n  \r\nAt this point London was rebuilding and upcycling these stretchers was seen as a fantastic opportunity to replace metal railings that had (during the war) been collected to use towards the war effort.  \r\n\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://hidden-history.com/public/assets/images/arp-stretchers-image2-mobile.jpg\" alt=\"Arp Stretchers\" width=\"auto\" height=\"auto\"> <sub><q>Stretchers in use <i>Source: wikimedia commons </i></q></sub>\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\nSadly, the number of surviving metal stretcher fences is falling due to their upkeep and the effects of the weather on them over the years but a lot of examples still exist today.  \r\n\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n\r\nIf you find yourself in this area be sure to keep an eye out for the wartime stretcher fences.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://hidden-history.com/public/assets/images/arp-stretchers-image3-mobile.jpg\" alt=\"Arp Stretchers\" width=\"auto\" height=\"auto\"> <sub><q>Stretcher fences at Down\'s estate. <i>Source: wikimedia commons </i></q></sub>', 'hankeyplace.jpg', 1, 0, 0, 77, '-0.088447', '51.499726', 0, 0, 1, 0, '', ''),
